SUMMARY:LBC Bike to 30K Program: Bike Check Up with Trek Bikes 
DESCRIPTION:Lancaster Bicycle Club (LBC) Meetup\nThe Bike to 30K is hostin
 g a Bike Check up with Trek Bikes! Bring your bike to Trek Bikes for a ser
 vice consult.\n\n**Grab your helmets\, bikes\, and sneakers — Lancaster 
 Bicycle Club is gearing up for beginner and transitional rides!** Local me
 mbers of the LBC are thrilled to host this year’s **Bike to 30K Program*
 *\, designed especially for new\, returning\, and curious cyclists.\n\n## 
 **About the Program**\n\nBike to 30K is a seven‑week series that gently 
 builds your confidence\, fitness\, and mileage. We begin with a five‑mil
 e ride and gradually work up to eighteen miles by the end of the program. 
 Our goal is simple: to introduce riders of all experience levels to the jo
 y of cycling in a supportive\, community‑focused environment.\nThis prog
 ram is **FREE** with an LBC membership — and membership is also free. Th
 e Bike to 30K program is open to everyone in our community who wants to ri
 de.\n\n## **Why We Ride**\n\nEver wonder why cyclists keep coming back? Be
 cause it’s fun. There’s nothing like coasting downhill and letting out
  a big “weeeeeee” all the way to the bottom. But we also know that if 
 you’re new to cycling\, jumping straight into an 18‑mile ride can feel
  intimidating. That’s exactly why Bike to 30K exists.\nEach week\, you
 ’ll increase your mileage at a comfortable pace. You’ll get to know th
 e club\, meet fellow riders\, and gradually grow into a confident **Fun Ri
 der** — the group known for enjoying scenic\, social rides together.\n\n
 ## **Our Commitment to You**\n\nLancaster Bicycle Club is dedicated to sup
 porting new riders and helping our community reach their cycling goals. Bi
 ke to 30K is part of our initiative to encourage more people to get outsid
 e\, get active\, and discover how enjoyable cycling can be.\nSpend seven w
 eeks with us and watch yourself transform into a Fun Rider — one mile at
  a time.\nThe Bike to 30K program is voluntary\, welcoming\, and designed 
 with beginners in mind. We can’t wait to ride with you.\n\n## **Membersh
 ip\, Waiver & RSVP Requirements**\n\nTo eliminate passing around a pen‑a
 nd‑paper waiver\, we require both:\n\n* **LBC Club Membership**\, and\n*
  **Meetup RSVP**\n\nYour RSVP allows us to contact you after the ride if n
 eeded. Please note: **ONLY club members who RSVP are covered by the club
 ’s excess accident insurance policy.** Being on Meetup does *not* mean y
 ou are a club member. To join our wonderful club\, please sign up through 
 our membership link.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lancaster-bicycle-club/events/3132615
 34/
